{
  "message": "feat(writing/slack-mattermost): rebuild OG + Twitter share images around the hero illustration\n\nUntil this commit, the Open Graph and Twitter cards for the Slack \u2192\nMattermost piece used an abstract SVG \"hash \u2192 arrow \u2192 chevron\"\ngraphic. That was fine, but the article now has a proper hero\nillustration (the Slack-bot-agents-migrating-to-Mattermost scene), so\nthe share images should reuse it. Scrolls, linked cards, and tweet\npreviews now carry the same visual brand as the article itself.\n\n------------------------------------------------------------\n 1. og-illustration.png (NEW)\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\nA 720x576 PNG crop of the hero illustration, colocated next to the\ntwo image routes in `app/writing/slack-mattermost-migration/`.\nPNG specifically because Satori (the engine behind `next/og`) silently\ncrashes on WebP with `TypeError: u2 is not iterable`, producing a\n0-byte 200-response that shows as a broken preview on every platform.\nPNG at 646 KB is the smallest usable format for the full-detail\nillustration at this size.\n\nColocated with the image routes rather than served from `/public/`\nso that the OG handler can load it synchronously from the same\nbundle via `new URL(\"./og-illustration.png\", import.meta.url)` \u2014\nno origin fetch, no first-deploy chicken-and-egg on the image not\nbeing cached yet, no CDN invalidation step.\n\n------------------------------------------------------------\n 2. opengraph-image.tsx + twitter-image.tsx rewrite\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\nSame layout and palette for both (1200x630 for OG, 1200x600 for\nTwitter). Left column: the illustration inside a rounded,\nsubtly-bordered frame with a cyan \u2192 purple radial glow behind it\n(matches the article's own hero placement). Right column: the\n\"AI Agents \u00b7 Infrastructure \u00b7 Cost\" label chip, the two-line title\nwith the purple \u2192 cyan \u2192 emerald gradient on the Slack line, a short\ndescription, and three color-coded feature chips\n(Slack \u2192 Mattermost, Claude Code \u00b7 Codex, Fail-Closed Cutover).\n\nThree large radial orbs (purple top-left, cyan mid, emerald\nbottom-right) provide the same editorial ambiance the article's\nhero uses. Subtle cyan grid at 4% opacity, bottom gradient accent\nbar, and the jeffreyemanuel.com watermark top-right to match the\nother share images on the site.\n\nImage load: `fetch(new URL(\"./og-illustration.png\", import.meta.url))`\nreads the file at OG-render time, `.arrayBuffer()` is passed\ndirectly to Satori's `<img src>` via an `as unknown as string` cast\n(Satori accepts ArrayBuffer even though the JSX types only allow\nstring; no runtime cost).\n\n------------------------------------------------------------\n Known Satori constraints respected\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\n- `display: flex` on every element\n- No `.map()` inside any `<svg>`\n- No `<polygon>`, `<text>`, `<br>`, or `strokeDasharray`\n- No `conic-gradient` (only linear / radial)\n- No CSS classes or Tailwind \u2014 inline styles only\n- No HTML entities in JSX text (contractions are inside `{\"...\"}`)\n- Inside every SVG, `viewBox` + explicit `width`/`height` attrs\n\n------------------------------------------------------------\n Metadata convention preserved\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\n`app/writing/slack-mattermost-migration/page.tsx` intentionally does\nNOT declare `openGraph.images` or `twitter.images`. That's on purpose:\nthe presence of those fields would kill Next.js's file-convention\nauto-detection of `opengraph-image.tsx` / `twitter-image.tsx` and\nwould strip the cache-busting hash from the `og:image` / `twitter:image`\nmeta tags. Kept `page.tsx` at just `title`, `description`, and\n`alternates.canonical`.\n\n------------------------------------------------------------\n Verified\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\n- `bun run build` \u2014 clean. Build manifest shows both image routes as\n  `\u0192` (dynamic), as required.\n- Local smoke test via `bun run start` on port 3477 + `curl`:\n    /writing/slack-mattermost-migration/opengraph-image  \u2192\n      HTTP 200, 753 KB, image/png, 1200x630 RGBA\n    /writing/slack-mattermost-migration/twitter-image    \u2192\n      HTTP 200, 706 KB, image/png, 1200x600 RGBA\n- Rendered output inspected: illustration reads cleanly on the left,\n  title gradient renders (purple \u2192 cyan \u2192 emerald), orbs + accent bar\n  + watermark all present.",
